NIST Dataplot is a software system for scientific visualization, statistical analysis, and non-linear modeling. 
Source code can be found at: https://github.com/usnistgov/dataplot
Dataplot's home page can be found at: https://www.itl.nist.gov/div898/software/dataplot/

To follow updates on new features go to: https://www.itl.nist.gov/div898/software/dataplot/news.htm

The platform is particularly useful extreme event modeling, processing modeling, and specifying experimental designs.
This directory contains resources for working with dataplot, and workflows using Dataplot in conjuction with R and Julia.
